      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "JET FUEL (1) chased the lead early from the inside and boxed on well to finish third, beaten 7 lengths (23.25) at this track in a Grade 5 over 400m. Comes out of a hot form race last start. Winning claims. MY WEE LASS (6) pinged the lids and led throughout to score last start (22.41) at Gosford in Grade 5 over 388m. Should be in this for a long way. ASTON PRESIDENT (2) showed little early speed at his last couple, the latest finishing sixth (18.03) in a Grade 5 at Taree Super Track. Solid record at the distance winning seven races. Has performed well from this box with a win and six minor placings to his name from 13 starts. Likely to be about the money. HOT TO RULE (7) has been in the placings at his last two runs, most recently when second (22.67) in a Grade 5 over 400m at Maitland.",
